The paper proposes a deep learning approach for individual recognition using EEG data in the context of schizophrenia. This involves developing modified deep learning architectures and evaluating their performance through various experiments. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves image processing techniques, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision). Lastly, the study involves human subjects and their brain activity, which could also fit with cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
